---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn what QuizNiva is and how it helps beginner learners practice."
  currentPath="/about"
>
  <section class="page-intro section">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Focused Study Practice</h1>
    <p>
      QuizNiva is a free learning site for short notes, examples, MCQs, and answer explanations across Python and Computer Fundamentals.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose prose--standalone">
    <h2>Who Publishes QuizNiva</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva is maintained by the QuizNiva Editorial Team. The site focuses on beginner-friendly technical education: programming basics, computer fundamentals, revision quizzes, and answer explanations. For corrections, suggestions, or policy questions, contact the team at <a class="text-link" href="mailto:contact@quizniva.in">contact@quizniva.in</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Who This Site Is For</h2>
    <p>
      This site is for students and self-learners who want a simple path through beginner topics. Each topic is designed to be read quickly, practiced immediately, and reviewed through explanations.
    </p>

    <h2>How The Content Works</h2>
    <p>
      Every finished topic has a lesson page and a quiz page. The lesson explains the idea with examples and common mistakes. The quiz checks understanding and shows explanations after submission.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial Approach</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva aims for clear language, original examples, and practice questions that match the lesson. Pages are reviewed for readability, factual accuracy, internal links, and learner usefulness before they are published. When a topic benefits from an external source, lessons link to trusted references such as official documentation or established educational resources.
    </p>

    <h2>What We Avoid</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva does not publish adult, violent, pirated, hateful, or dangerous content. The site also avoids misleading health or financial claims because its purpose is educational computing practice.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
